article.headline: Western Illinois 74, Texas-Arlington 57
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Sammy Hunter and David Jackson combined to score more than half of Western Illinois' points as the Leathernecks beat Texas-Arlington 74-57 Monday night. Hunter scored 21 points on 6-of-8 shooting from the field and 7-of-9 shooting from the foul line. Jackson, who also pulled down a team-high eight rebounds, added 19 points. He was just 4-for-14 from the field but hit 10 of 12 free throws. Texas-Arlington (3-4) got 18 points from Brandon Long, who shot 7-for-9 from the foul line and added three 3-pointers. Rodrick Epps chipped in 13 points. The Mavericks led 32-24 at the half, but Western Illinois (3-4) bounced back from 26 percent first-half shooting to outmatch Texas-Arlington in the second, when the Leathernecks converted 20 of 23 free-throw attempts.
